<h3>Description</h3>
<p>A data type for storing a 24/32-bit number, values of 0 to 2^24 or 2^32.</p>
<p>In TRSE, long is only defined for the following systems:
<ul>
<li>M68K (Amiga/Atari ST): 32-bit number
<li>X86: 32-bit number
<li>Mega64: 24-bit number (used for banked data)
</ul>
<h3>Example</h3>

<code>
    var
        data : long = 0;
</code>
